===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} ''[[leþer]]'', from {{proto|Germanic|''leþran''}} (cf. {{etyl|nl|-}}/{{etyl|de|-}} {{term|leder}}), from {{etyl|cel}} *''letrom'' (cf. {{etyl|cy|-}} {{term|lledr}}, {{etyl|ga|-}} {{term|lethar}}), from pre-Celtic *''péltrom'', from {{proto|Indo-European|''pel-''}} 'to beat'. More at [[anvil]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-leather.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɛðə(r)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# A tough material produced from the [[skin]] of [[animal]]s, by [[tan]]ning or similar process, used e.g. for [[clothing]].
# A piece of leather used for [[polish]]ing.
# (''colloquialism'') A [[cricket]] ball or [[football]].
# (''plural'': '''leathers''') Leather clothing, often worn by [[motorcycle]] riders.
# {{baseball}} A good defensive play
#: ''Jones showed good '''leather''' to snare that [[liner]].''

